-- Bayern Munich Opens Champions League Title Defense With 3-0 Win
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-09-17T20:46:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-17/bayern-munich-opens-champions-league-title-defense-with-3-0-win.html
Bayern Munich beat CSKA Moscow 3-0
on the opening night of soccer’s Champions League, while Real
Madrid routed Galatasaray 6-1.  David Alaba, Mario Mandzukic and  Arjen Robben  scored for
Bayern, which is looking to become the first team since AC Milan
in 1990 to defend its title in Europe’s elite club competition.
Three goals from Cristiano Ronaldo led record nine-time champion
Real Madrid.  Manchester United  beat Bayer Leverkusen 4-2, Manchester
City defeated Viktoria Plzen 3-0 and Paris Saint-Germain beat
Olympiacos 4-1. Benfica defeated Anderlecht 2-0, Shakhtar
Donetsk won 2-0 at Real Sociedad and Copenhagen drew 1-1 with
Juventus at home.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  